{
  "texts": [
    "See Section 5.4.2 for discussion.",
    "Table 2: Variation in point estimates across large language models and prompting strategies on financial news headlines.",
    "Notes: On financial news headlines from 2019, we prompt GPT-3.5-Turbo, GPT-4o-mini, and GPT-4o to label each headline for whether it expressed positive, negative or uncertain news about the respective company using alternative prompting strategies.",
    "For each model m and prompt p, we regress the realized returns of each stock within 1-day of the headline's publication date on each large language model's labels V m,p r, the large language model's assessed magnitude denoted S m,p r and their interaction, controlling for lagged realized returns.",
    "See Section 5.3.2 for discussion."
  ]
}